role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 17, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104twa1760609386094.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/twa1760609386094.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/twa1760609386094.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"twa1760609386094\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Allow users to debug their own 3GL components using a 3GL debugger.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"twa1760609386094__section_w1157ab1b5b1_w1158ab1b5_w1159ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING = TRUE | FALSE</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"twa1760609386094__section_b1b_4lq_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d487263e56\">Defaults </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"twa1760609386094__table_d16874e1_d16875e1_d16876e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">application assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">FALSE </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"twa1760609386094__section_elg_4lq_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d487263e102\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING</span> is set to\n\t\t\t\t\t<kbd class=\"ph userinput\">TRUE</kbd>,  you can attach a 3GL debugger to an already\n\t\t\t\trunning instance of Uniface to debug your own 3GL components. This helps in avoiding\n\t\t\t\tany interference to some of the operations Uniface performs. This applies both to\n\t\t\t\t3GL components that run using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">activate</code> statement and those run\n\t\t\t\tusing the <code class=\"ph codeph\">perform</code> statement. If your 3GL debugger starts Uniface,\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING</span> will be set to TRUE\n\t\t\t\tautomatically.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Also, when <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING</span> is set to TRUE, it disables\n\t\t\t\tdecryption of settings encrypted by the Pathscrambler, so your assignment files must\n\t\t\t\tnot have been generated by the Pathscrambler. </p>\n<p class=\"p\">This setting needs to be included in the assignment file of the application process\n\t\t\t\tthat is actually running the 3GL component to be debugged. It should never be placed\n\t\t\t\tin the URouter assignment file, as URouter ignores it. Typically, it should not be\n\t\t\t\tadded in the UServer assignment file either—unless that specific UServer is running\n\t\t\t\tthe 3GL component. In such cases, the client application's assignment file must also\n\t\t\t\tinclude the setting.</p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"twa1760609386094__note_lk3_bwm_zgc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You must use\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING</span> setting in your development\n\t\t\t\t\tenvironments only, and not in a production environment. A deployed application\n\t\t\t\t\tshould never have this setting in any of its assignment files.</div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"twa1760609386094__section_uqk_4lq_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle exampletitle\" id=\"twa1760609386094__p_d140285e1_d140286e1_d140287e1\">Example:\n\t\t\t\t$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"twa1760609386094__pre_p3q_cmq_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING = TRUE</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_21600480\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_21600480\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 17, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Allow users to debug their own 3GL components using a 3GL debugger. $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING = TRUE | FALSE Defaults Assignment file: application assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: FALSE Description When $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING is set to TRUE , you can attach a 3GL debugger to an already running instance of Uniface to debug your own 3GL components. This helps in avoiding any interference to some of the operations Uniface performs. This applies both to 3GL components that run using the activate statement and those run using the perform statement. If your 3GL debugger starts Uniface, $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING will be set to TRUE automatically. Also, when $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING is set to TRUE, it disables decryption of settings encrypted by the Pathscrambler, so your assignment files must not have been generated by the Pathscrambler. This setting needs to be included in the assignment file of the application process that is actually running the 3GL component to be debugged. It should never be placed in the URouter assignment file, as URouter ignores it. Typically, it should not be added in the UServer assignment file either—unless that specific UServer is running the 3GL component. In such cases, the client application's assignment file must also include the setting. Note: You must use $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING setting in your development environments only, and not in a production environment. A deployed application should never have this setting in any of its assignment files. Example: $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING $ENABLE_USER_3GL_DEBUGGING = TRUE Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}